{"questionId":"3070038","questionHtml":"<p>Find an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempts to express <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math> with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <em><strong>(M1) </strong></em>if<em> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;</em>is used.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>uses <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>uses <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>uses <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3070038","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ2.2gi","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find an expression for r1 in terms of b.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.10—Solving equations graphically and analytically"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}